<!--Create a Triangle class.
Make a web page that lets the user input the lengths of the sides of a Triangle, and tells whether they form an equilateral, isosceles, or scalene triangle. If you're not familiar with these terms, here are definitions:
equilateral: all sides are equal;
isosceles: exactly 2 sides are equal;
scalene: no sides are equal.
Keep in mind that not all combinations of three numbers make valid triangles. For example, (2, 2, 8) does not make a triangle. The rule is that any side is longer than the other two combined, the lengths do not form a triangle.-->
